# COP Cursor Rules — v0.2.0-alpha.1
# Applied when editing any file in this repository.

You are working on the Cognitive Object Protocol (COP) repository.

When editing .cop.json files:
- Use operation patches. Never rewrite the whole document.
- Preserve all existing id values. Never overwrite id via update_block.
- Do NOT set trust_level to "human_reviewed" — only humans may do this.
- Do NOT use trust_level "verified" — it does not exist in v0.1.
- Do NOT create instruction blocks without explicit human request.
- All agent operations must have status: "proposed".
- Run `copctl validate <file>` after editing.

Before proposing update_block or change_state:
1. Run: copctl hash <file> --target <blockId>
2. Include the hash as preconditions.target_hash

Supported ops: update_block, change_state, create_block, add_relation, add_comment, resolve_comment

Response format:
{
  "operations": [{
    "id": "op_<id>",
    "op": "update_block",
    "target": "blk_...",
    "actor": { "type": "agent", "name": "cursor" },
    "patch_format": "json_patch",
    "patch": [{ "op": "replace", "path": "/content/text", "value": "..." }],
    "preconditions": { "target_hash": "sha256:..." },
    "reason": "...",
    "status": "proposed",
    "created_at": "<ISO>"
  }]
}

See AGENTS.md for full rules.
